main event: A slow moving bright white object with a shallow zig-zag flight pattern was observed moving across the sky from overhead to the southeast horizon in Dorchester, Massachusetts on May 30, 1964.
interesting points: The object was observed for about 5 minutes.
The object was described as bright white in color.
The object moved in a shallow zig-zag flight pattern.
The object was estimated to be at an altitude of 2,000-2,500 feet above the horizon.
Several other people in the area also observed the object at around 9:57 PM on the same date.
sighted object: a bright white, slow moving object with a zig-zag flight pattern
